Edition:
Quote: /r/ is pronounced as in RP, but its more frequent occurrence in Otago and Southland may be noted. It marks what is sometimes called the Southland burr, in which /r/ is pronounced in words such as <i>dark</i> or <i>word</i> where it is lost in RP.
